-- Investec, Murray & Roberts, Vodacom: South African Equity Market Preview
-- B y   V e r n o n   W e s s e l s
-- 2011-02-03T05:59:12Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-02-02/bidvest-firestone-energy-imperial-vodacom-south-african-equity-preview.html
The following is a list of companies
whose shares may have unusual price changes in  South Africa .
Stock symbols are in parentheses after company names and prices
are from the last close.  South Africa’s FTSE/JSE Africa All Share Index climbed
649.45, or 2 percent, to 32,487.61 at the 5 p.m. close in
Johannesburg.    First Uranium Corp . (FUM SJ): The producer of the mineral
said revenue for the three months ended Dec. 31 rose 60 percent
from a year ago. The stock was unchanged at 7.49 rand.    Great Basin Gold Ltd . (GBG SJ): The gold explorer said
mineral reserves increased 55 percent to 140,000 recovered gold
ounces. The shares added 76 cents, or 4 percent, to 19.59 rand.    Investec Ltd . (INL SJ): The private bank and wealth manager
releases an interim management statement. The stock increased 79
cents, or 1.4 percent, to 56.07 rand.  Murray & Roberts Ltd. (MUR SJ): The construction company
was raised to “overweight” from “neutral” by JPMorgan Chase
& Co. The shares fell 9 cents, or 0.3 percent, to 29.56 rand.    Optimum Coal Holdings  Ltd. (OPT SJ): The coal producer said
net profit rose to 274.6 million rand ($38 million) in the six
months through December from 69.7 million rand a year earlier.
The stock was unchanged at 33 rand.    Vodacom Group Ltd . (VOD SJ): The largest provider of
mobile-phone services to South Africans had its price estimate
raised to 57 rand from 54 rand at Goldman Sachs Group Inc.
Vodacom shares climbed 3.22 rand, or 4.5 percent, to 74.50 rand.  Shares or American depositary receipts of the following South
African companies closed as follows:  Anglo American Plc (AAUKY US) rose 2.9 percent to $26.32.
AngloGold Ashanti Ltd. (AU US) dropped 0.8 percent to $44.23.
BHP Billiton Ltd. (BBL US) added 2.6 percent to $81.11. DRDGold
Ltd. (DROOY US) gained 0.4 percent to $4.59. Gold Fields Ltd.
(GFI US) was little changed at $16.12. Harmony Gold Mining Co.
(HMY US) slipped 2.5 percent to $10.73. Impala Platinum Holdings
(IMPUY US) climbed 0.5 percent to $29.31. Sappi Ltd. (SPP US)
rose 0.2 percent to $5.39. Sasol Ltd. (SSL US) lost 1 percent to
$49.14.  To contact the reporter on this story:
